The paper deals with the problem of learning large Gaussian mixtures, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), such as tensor decompositions and Independent Component Analysis (ICA), to solve the problem of mixture recovery. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to embedding difficult instances of low-dimensional Gaussian mixtures into the ICA setting, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
